# All build output (ADR-0021): the cargo target dirs (build/engine, build/xtask),
# the C# bin output (build/app), the publish bundle (build/dist), release packages
# (build/package), release SBOMs (build/sbom) and the staged docs site (build/site,
# build/docs-book) — one tree, one ignore line.
build/

# Cargo's default target dir. Build output normally lands under build/ via each
# workspace's .cargo/config.toml (ADR-0021); but a cargo run that bypasses that
# config — `cargo --manifest-path <ws>/Cargo.toml` from the repo root, or some
# rust-analyzer / IDE invocations — falls back to <ws>/target. Ignore it
# everywhere so stray artifacts can never be committed and hooks (typos) skip
# them. (Covers engine/target, xtask/target, engine/fuzz/target.)
target/

# C# intermediate output stays in-tree: relocating obj needs a
# Directory.Build.props, which CLAUDE.md forbids (ADR-0021).
app/**/obj/

# IDE / editor state
.vs/
*.user

# Test + coverage artifacts produced outside build/
screenshots/
test-results.json
**/*.cobertura.xml
# winapp UI-automation run output (screenshots + results JSON)
app/FindMyFiles.Tests/UiAutomation/artifacts/
# coverlet raw coverage output (sibling of the ignored *.cobertura.xml)
app/FindMyFiles.Tests/coverage.json
# dotnet test default TRX / sequence output (regenerable per run)
app/FindMyFiles.Tests/TestResults/
# llvm-cov line-coverage report written into engine/ by the CI gate / `just cov`
# (cargo llvm-cov --output-path engine-lcov.info).
engine-lcov.info
# cargo-mutants run output. Its `mutants.out{,.old}/` dir model sits next to the
# engine workspace and does not compose with the build/ redirect (ADR-0021), so
# ignore it in place — it is CI/machine-local, regenerated on every run.
engine/mutants.out*/

# Engine runtime artifacts
*.fmfidx
engine/crates/fmf-core/testdata/large/

# cargo-fuzz working output. Its dir model (corpus/artifacts next to the fuzz
# crate) does not compose with the build/ redirect (ADR-0021), so ignore these
# in place; they are nightly, CI-only, machine-local. (fuzz/target is covered by
# the top-level target/ rule.) The committed Cargo.lock is kept for reproducibility.
engine/fuzz/corpus/
engine/fuzz/artifacts/
engine/fuzz/coverage/

# Local-only tool overrides
mise.local.toml
.mise.local.toml

# npm deps pulled into the tree by the actionlint action (CI hygiene job);
# never committed, but keep an accidental local `act`/action run out of git.
node_modules/

# Claude Code local working dir (scheduled task locks, etc.)
.claude/

# Internal working notes — never publish
CLAUDE.md

# Untracked screenshot scratch
.tmp-shots/
